						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Ministers-promise-decade-for-African-science" title="Ministers promise decade for African science" alt="link">Ministers promise decade for African science</a></h2>

	
					<p>African science ministers concluded a high-level meeting in Egypt by declaring 2011-2020 the &quot;decade for science in Africa&quot;. The decision, taken at the end of the African Ministerial Council on Science and Technology (AMCOST) meeting 7 until 10 March, will aim to keep science and technology at the forefront of the continent's political agenda. The decision was made in recognition of &quot;the challenges that African Union (AU) member states are facing in harnessing science and technology (S&amp;T) for socio-economic development and the need to sensitise the African Community and to engage the AU leaders in S&amp;T&quot;. (Source All Africa, 19 March 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">26/04/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
