						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/East-African-scientists-to-form-new-disease-surveillance-centre" title="East African scientists to form new disease surveillance centre " alt="link">East African scientists to form new disease surveillance centre </a></h2>

	
					<p>








 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/east-african-scientists/299066-1-eng-GB/East-African-Scientists.jpg" rel="lightbox[]">	
	  </a>
	
		
			
	
  	






	 
  





	Scientists from five East African countries, Burundi, Kenya, Rwanda, Tanzania and Uganda will establish a regional disease surveillance centre which will link medical and veterinary institutions to improve their capacity to detect, identify and monitor infectious diseases in plants, animals and humans. The East African Centre for Infectious Disease Surveillance (EACIDS) will will also increase laboratory capacities and harmonise and standardise best practices and facilitate the sharing of data and communication. This initiative was supported by FAO. (Source: The Observer, 17 March 2010)</p>
